<br>
The guild cant help but be sub-divided based on skill levels...I suggest a leader at each level.  These leaders will promote the daily functions of the guild at their level, organize raids for their level, keep in touch with new recruits, chose the &quot;base camp&quot; for that level, etc...<br>
<br>
The levels would approximately be 20-30, 30-40, 40-50, 50 plus.  The levels would not be rigid, a character could move to the 30-40 group at 29 if he so chose, but 26 would be too early.<br>
<br>
The level leader would lead his group until his character matured to where he wanted to be promoted to next level.   Upon promotion, the level leader would loose his &quot;title&quot; and a new leader would then be chosen to fill the vacancy.<br>
<br>
The level leader must actively play his character. It must be his main character at that time, although it may not be his highest character.<br>
<br>
I would envision the level leaders to be changing often, every month or so, to give anyone a chance to serve the guild.  Additionally, after a few months, fresh blood would bring new enthusiam to the leader position<br>
<br>
This would be an appointed position by guild leader or board, as determined by the group<br>
<br>
As our guild struggles to continue and grow, leadership and planning at each stage is important.  A level 52 player has different wants and desires than a 19 player.  I think this might help us provide more player satisfaction to all players, and might help us have better player retention in our guild.<br>
<br>
Your responses appreciated<br>
<br>
Medicin<br>
Cleric of the 51st Season<br>
